Here is a JSON object that represents the desired template:
```json
{
  "page": "XXXX",
  "function": [
    {
      "function": "XXX",
      "parameter": [
        {
          "name": "XXX",
          "answer": "<your_answer_parameter>"
        },
        {...}, ...
      ]
    },
    {...}, ...,
  ],
  {...}, ...
}
```
Replace `XXXX` with the name of the page you want to test. Replace `XXX` with the name of the function you want to test. Replace `<your_answer_parameter>` with the desired answer for the parameter you want to provide. The other parameters and their respective values can be added or removed as needed.

For example, if you want to test the `login` function on the `help` page with the parameter `username`, you would create a JSON object like this:
```json
{
  "page": "Help",
  "function": [
    {
      "function": "login",
      "parameter": [
        {
          "name": "username",
          "answer": "admin"
        }
      ]
    },
    {...}, ...,
  ],
  {...}, ...
}
```
